Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 110, 48 or 163, 28. Name Euphranor. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0125.36.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0727)
